This document is a two-page "IBM Batch Report" for `Electoral Event ID 19694`, `Vote Collection Point Bangor (ID 2178)`, and `Batch Number 3` in `NSW`, generated on June 15, 2016. It details the processing of 50 individual ballots within this specific batch. For each ballot, the report provides the status of numerous processing checks, including `Quality Assurance Checked`, `Initials Checked`, `Official Mark Checked`, `Unusual Markings Checked`, `Formality Result Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Preferences Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, `BTL Preferences Checked`, and `BTL Mismatches`, among others. Notably, all entries for all 50 ballots in this specific report indicate "OK" across all checks, signifying successful processing without any detected anomalies or issues.

This document is highly relevant to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] as it is a direct example of the "IBM Batch Report" files sought. It provides concrete evidence of the type of detailed ballot processing information, including batch metadata and individual ballot check statuses, that the request aimed to uncover. While the FOI overview notes the frequent occurrence of "HAS ISSUES" entries in these reports, this particular document illustrates a "clean" batch where all checks passed, providing a complete picture of the range of processing outcomes recorded by the system.

Do not include any conversational filler or preamble.To aid you, the overview of the FOI request is: [REQUEST OVERVIEW START] Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] sought documents related to 'IBM Outputs' from 2016, yielding 106 "IBM Batch Report" PDF files dated June 8, 10, and 15, 2016, categorized by Vote Collection Point and Batch Number. These detailed reports provide insights into ballot processing, including batch metadata, electoral event context, and specific ballot-level checks for formality, initials, marks, and preferences (ATL/BTL). While most entries indicate "OK" for successful processing, various checks, notably `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, and `BTL Mismatches`, frequently show "HAS ISSUES" entries, often accompanied by alphanumeric codes (e.g., D2, Y9, M1, U1), signifying specific anomalies or exceptions in the ballot processing.
